The Clubs Carnival is just around the corner, and it’s the perfect time to explore all the amazing clubs on campus. 🎪
Swing by the French Course Unison table to say bonjour! Come learn about French at UofT, meet some new friends, and discover more about what we do. Can’t wait to see you all there!
It will be on Friday August 30th, 2024 from 1pm-4pm at Front Canpus, and we will be Table D20!

Le carnaval des clubs approche à grands pas et c’est le moment idéal pour découvrir tous les clubs incroyables au campus. 🎪
Passez par la table du Réseau des cours de français pour dire bonjour! Venez en apprendre davantage sur le français à l’UofT, discuter, rencontrer de nouveaux amis et découvrir ce que nous faisons. Nous avons hâte de vous voir!
Ça sera le vendredi 30 août 2024, de 13h à 16h au Front Campus et nous serons à la table D20!

Aug 14 - Desert Workshop 🐪
•
Our last workshop of the summer took place a bit over a week ago!! Hope you all had a restful summer and looking forward to seeing you all in the fall :))
•

Hey folders!!

🐪🌵☀️🦎🐫🏜️

Thankfully it seems like the summer heat has passed already :’))) It has been so hot for the last few weeks but I’m so happy to finally be able to head outside without immediately breaking a sweat 😩  Despite our relatively cooler summer weather, we’re hosting this week’s workshop in the clubroom so it’s about to feel like peak summer weather all over again 😭  This week, we’re hosting a 🏜️ desert themed workshop, featuring models of camels and cacti :00

This week’s workshop will take place 📆 Wednesday, August 14th, from 🕔  5 - 7 PM in 📍 Meeting Room 503 in the Sussex Club house (21 Sussex Ave). Diagrams and origami paper will be provided!

This week’s models include:
☀️ Origami Sun (Jo Nakashima)
🌵  Potted Cactus
🐪  Dromedary (John Montroll)
🐫  Camel (John Montroll)

If you’re planning to attend, please let us know by indicating your interest on the Discord event in our server (link to join in our bio)

This will be our last workshop before the school year starts!! Hope to see you all on Wednesday :)

🐪🌵☀️🦎🐫🏜️

Thank you once again to our lovely Director of Art Daniel🫡
